    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is offset by the strong performance of all other factors and by the direct regulatory precedent of ASTM F1717 as the accepted test standard for pedicle screw submissions. Validation metrics (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference < 10%) satisfied for all three quantities of interest across two independent laboratories. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level for this Class II device application.",
